@node "install" "Usage"

 Select a game from the listview with the currently loaded patch base
 and click on one of the following buttons:

 Start Patching: This patches the currently selected game. After pressing
 this button Da Cool Patcher will load in the patch and ask you for a file
 of the selected game/program which will be patched. After you`ve selected
 this file DCP will check if you got the correct version and then the file
 will be patched. If the game is disk-only you`ve to insert the disk and DCP
 will do the same procedure as above but from disk.

 Start Unpatching: This unpatches the currently selected game. Unpatching
 can be useful if a patch doesn`t work with a game.

 Patch Editor: With the Patch Editor you can create your own patches. After
 you`ve pressed this button a new window will open. In that window you have
 to type some information like game`s name, game`s developer, patch author etc.
 and you need of course specify the patch offset and the patches. It`s also
 possible to import patches in the Patch Editor: Click the 'Import' button
 and then on a patch in the main listview. If you click on 'Save' the patch will
 be saved to the user patchbase.

 About: Displays some information about the program 

 Exit: Quits Da Cool Patcher.

@endnode

